{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/readabilityjs-adding-reader-view/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"itsopensource"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"45ad1bfa-7ed6-56f3-8d02-45be69ffed29","excerpt":"One of the features I absolutely love in Firefox is . This removes all the clutter and present the content in text format for better readability and relief for‚Ä¶","html":"<p>\nOne of the features I absolutely love in Firefox is <code class=\"language-text\">Firefox Reader View</code>. This removes all the clutter and present the content in text format for better readability and relief for eyes(It also removes the ad banners üòâ ).</p>\n<p>Not all the browsers (Chrome needs special flag to enable this üòê ) have a readability mode thus, providing an option for reader mode within your website would be a huge help to your users and would make your webpage more accessible.  </p>\n<p>The good news is you do not have to implement this on your own, Mozilla has a standalone version of the readability library used for Firefox Reader View - <a href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/readability\"><strong>Readability.js</strong></a>.<br>\nThe usage is pretty simple and straight forward:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>We need to include the readability.js in our code in either of 2 ways:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Download the file via <a href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/readability/releases\">https://github.com/mozilla/readability/releases</a></li>\n<li>Install npm package - <a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@mozilla/readability\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/@mozilla/readability</a></li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Create a new <code class=\"language-text\">Readabilty</code> object from DOM document node</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> article <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Readability</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>document<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This article object will have following properties</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">title</code>: article title</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">content</code>: HTML string of processed article content</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">textContent</code>: text content of the article (all HTML removed)</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">length</code>: length of an article, in characters</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">excerpt</code>: article description, or short excerpt from the content</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">byline</code>: author metadata</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">dir</code>: content direction (LTR or RTL)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Note</em> Readability morphs the actual object so better to pass a clone node.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> documentClone <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">cloneNode</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> article <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Readability</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>documentClone<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">parse</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>Substitute this <code class=\"language-text\">article.textContent</code> in the desired div and done üòé</li>\n</ol>\n<p>See this in action here - <a href=\"https://itsopensource.com/demos/readability\">https://itsopensource.com/demos/readability</a></p>\n<p><strong><center>HTML View</center></strong></p>\n<p>  <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/85c72003e8f4f49d3eca4602b5e591b3/9cab2/html.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60.13513513513513%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"HTML view\"\n        title=\"HTML view\"\n        src=\"/static/85c72003e8f4f49d3eca4602b5e591b3/fcda8/html.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/85c72003e8f4f49d3eca4602b5e591b3/12f09/html.png 148w,\n/static/85c72003e8f4f49d3eca4602b5e591b3/e4a3f/html.png 295w,\n/static/85c72003e8f4f49d3eca4602b5e591b3/fcda8/html.png 590w,\n/static/85c72003e8f4f49d3eca4602b5e591b3/9cab2/html.png 864w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong><center>Text View</center></strong></p>\n<p>  <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/544a4f228aa2058fd233d61355f4c31c/66caf/text.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.10810810810811%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"text view\"\n        title=\"text view\"\n        src=\"/static/544a4f228aa2058fd233d61355f4c31c/fcda8/text.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/544a4f228aa2058fd233d61355f4c31c/12f09/text.png 148w,\n/static/544a4f228aa2058fd233d61355f4c31c/e4a3f/text.png 295w,\n/static/544a4f228aa2058fd233d61355f4c31c/fcda8/text.png 590w,\n/static/544a4f228aa2058fd233d61355f4c31c/66caf/text.png 853w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Reference: <a href=\"https://github.com/mozilla/readability\">https://github.com/mozilla/readability</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"ReadabilityJS - adding Reader View Mode to websites","tags":["accessibility","javascript","firefox"],"date":"January 17, 2021","description":null,"author":"trishul","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.5267175572519085,"src":"/static/a81f4730a5edd277214c22c33052a025/46604/readability.png","srcSet":"/static/a81f4730a5edd277214c22c33052a025/69585/readability.png 200w,\n/static/a81f4730a5edd277214c22c33052a025/497c6/readability.png 400w,\n/static/a81f4730a5edd277214c22c33052a025/46604/readability.png 500w","sizes":"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/readabilityjs-adding-reader-view/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/publish-github-pages-with-github-actions/"},"frontmatter":{"au